
### Core Components
* **QWidget**
    The base class for all UI objects. It is a generic, empty container. 
    Every visual element—from a single button to the entire main window—is technically a widget.

### Layout Managers
Layouts are invisible containers that automatically handle the positioning and resizing of your widgets.

* **QHBoxLayout**
    Arranges widgets horizontally (side-by-side) in a linear row.
* **QVBoxLayout**
    Arranges widgets vertically (stacked) in a linear column.

### Key Methods
* **addWidget(widget, stretch)**
    Adds a specific UI element (like a button or input field) to a layout.
    * The **stretch** integer defines how much space a widget takes relative to others (e.g., using 7 and 3 makes one widget take up 70% of the space).
* **addLayout(layout, stretch)**
    Used for nesting layouts. This allows you to place a horizontal row of buttons inside a vertical column of text fields.
* **setLayout(layout)**
    The final step for your main class. It instructs the widget to use a specific layout to organize its children.

### Sizing & Responsiveness
* **setSizePolicy(...)**
    Defines how a widget behaves when the window is resized. 
    This ensures that buttons or text fields dynamically expand and fill available space instead of remaining at a fixed size.
